{
  "info": {
    "name": "KillShill Signal Tracker API",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the KillShill Trading Signal Tracker application.\n\n## Base URL\n`http://localhost:5000`\n\n## Overview\nThis API allows you to create and manage trading signals with live Binance price integration.\n\n## Signal Status Flow\n- `OPEN` → Signal is active and being tracked\n- `TARGET_HIT` → Price reached target level (locked forever)\n- `STOPLOSS_HIT` → Price hit stop loss level (locked forever)\n- `EXPIRED` → Signal expired without hitting target or stop loss (locked forever)\n\n## Validation Rules\n**BUY:** stop_loss < entry_price < target_price\n**SELL:** target_price < entry_price < stop_loss\n\n## ROI Formula\n**BUY ROI:** (current_price - entry_price) / entry_price × 100\n**SELL ROI:** (entry_price - current_price) / entry_price × 100",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the backend server"
    },
    {
      "key": "signalId",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-set after creating a signal — used in single signal requests"
    },
    {
      "key": "deleteSignalId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-set before delete test"
    }
  ],
